Linux Package Managers â€“ APT & YUM : Both automate software management
Package managers help you install, update, remove, and manage software on Linux systems while automatically handling dependencies.
e.g. nginx ko install krne ke liye required libraries are: libc openssl pcre but ðŸ‘‰ APT / YUM / DNF automatically ye sab install kar dete hain
Aapko manually yaad rakhne ki zarurat nahi.

1. apt-->(Advanced Package Tool)APT is the default package manager for Debian-based Linux distributions.
    Package Format  --> .deb
ðŸ”¹ Used In
Ubuntu    ,  Debian ,  Linux Mint  ,   Pop!_OS
ðŸ”¹ Command: sudo apt install nginx

ðŸ”¹ Common APT Commands
| Task                       | Command                  |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Update package list        | `sudo apt update`        |
| Upgrade installed packages | `sudo apt upgrade`       |
| Install package            | `sudo apt install nginx` |
| Remove package             | `sudo apt remove nginx`  |
| Remove + config files      | `sudo apt purge nginx`   |
| Search package             | `apt search nginx`       |
| Package info               | `apt show nginx`         |

APT in DevOps: Used in Dockerfiles
               CI/CD pipelines on Ubuntu runners
               Cloud VM provisioning (EC2 Ubuntu)
sudo apt update              # repo se latest list lao
sudo apt install nginx       # install
sudo apt upgrade             # upgrade packages
sudo apt remove nginx        # remove
sudo apt purge nginx         # remove + config
apt search docker            # search
apt show nginx               # details

2. YUM --> (Yellowdog Updater Modified) YUM is the package manager for RPM-based Linux distributions (older systems).
    Used In : CentOS 7, RHEL 7, Amazon Linux 1 & 2
  Package Format   >  .rpm
ðŸ”¹ Common YUM Commands
| Task            | Command                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------ |
| Install package | `sudo yum install nginx` |
| Update packages | `sudo yum update`        |
| Remove package  | `sudo yum remove nginx`  |
| Search package  | `yum search nginx`       |
| Package info    | `yum info nginx`         |
| List installed  | `yum list installed`     |

ðŸ”¹ YUM in DevOps Widely used in > enterprise servers, Amazon Linux EC2 instance,s Legacy production environments.
  sudo yum install -y docker
âš ï¸ Note: YUM is now replaced by DNF(Dandified YUM) in newer systems (CentOS 8+, RHEL 8+)

ðŸ”¹An 'update' refreshes the package lists, while an 'upgrade' actually installs new versions of
packages.
ðŸ”¹Dependencies: Additional packages required by a software package. 
ðŸ”¹Dependency resolution means automatically finding and installing required packages.

ðŸ”¹ Why updates are critical?
Security patches
Bug fixes
Performance improvements
Compatibility with new software

ðŸ“Œ DevOps reality:
Outdated packages = security vulnerability.

